<heading>joins groups - List groups for a user.</heading>

<rule/>

<heading level="2">
Usage
</heading>

<pre>
  groups USER
</pre>

<heading level="2">
Description
</heading>

<paragraph>
Lists all groups that a user belongs to.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
Examples
</heading>

<pre>
groups bob
  List all groups bob is a member of.

joins/groups alice
  From another space, qualifies the path.
</pre>

<heading level="2">
See also
</heading>

<paragraph>
add, remove, users
</paragraph>
